  <p>
 
    <xref outputclass="element"
            keyref="element_emergency_care_acuity__snomed_ct_">EMERGENCY CARE ACUITY (SNOMED CT)</xref>
 is the same as attribute 
    <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_clinical_terminology_code">CLINICAL TERMINOLOGY CODE</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
      <xref outputclass="element"
            keyref="element_emergency_care_acuity__snomed_ct_">EMERGENCY CARE ACUITY (SNOMED CT)</xref>
 is the 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/clinical_coding/snomed_ct.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">SNOMED_CT</xref>
® concept ID which is used to indicate the acuity of the 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
's condition on the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_emergency_care_initial_assessment_date">Emergency Care Initial Assessment Date</xref>
 and 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_emergency_care_initial_assessment_time">Emergency Care Initial Assessment Time</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
The 
    <xref outputclass="element"
            keyref="element_emergency_care_acuity__snomed_ct_">EMERGENCY CARE ACUITY (SNOMED CT)</xref>
 may be determined by a formal triage process, or by the physical allocation of the 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 to a specific clinical area such as Resuscitation.  </p>
